reviewText: Good railroad history telling of the signals and brakes

The film itself offers next to nothing, except perhaps for steam locomotive fans and those interested in seeing Jean Arthur in a silent role. Both will be disappointed because the picture quality is so bad. At times, Arthur's face is no more than two holes, for her eyes, in a white blob. Really, there is nothing here worth spending $$ on.
Couldn't finish due to poor picture quality.  I know it is an Alpha release but I was hoping for the best.
